               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420404-name-628" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-628" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-628" type="surname" value="HUNT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-628" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM HUNT</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the service of Robert Watt, a pawnbroker in Exmouth-street, Clerkenwell. Between two and three o'clock in the after<lb></lb>noon of the 18th of March, I saw the prisoner in ray master's shop, looking at a child's pinafore—she put the pinafore down, drew this handkerchief from under the goods, and put it under her child's cloak—she was going out of the door—I told her to come back and put that down—she came back and put it down—she turned round, and said she had got nothing—a policeman was sent for, and she was given into custody.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420404-name-629" type="witnessName">
